<body>

<h1>QQQ/QLD Signal Desk - Real Account Tracking System</h1>

<p>This document is the operating manual for the QQQ/QLD Signal Desk dashboard. The dashboard is the daily live display. This Word-readable file defines the rules, data source, update process, and what to do when the model shows Cash, QQQ, QQQ + QLD, or QLD.</p>

<div class="note">
Main version to track: <b>QLD / QQQ / Cash with 5-Day DCA from QQQ to QLD</b>. Signal source is <b>QQQ</b>. Leveraged holding is <b>QLD</b>. Benchmark language remains <b>QQQ Hold</b>. Cash is a normal model state.
</div>

<h2>1. Dashboard Purpose</h2>

<p>The dashboard should answer these questions after the daily update:</p>

<ol>
<li>What is the current model state: Cash, QQQ, QQQ + QLD, or QLD?</li>
<li>What is the plain-English status: Hold Cash, Hold QQQ, DCA to QLD, or Hold QLD?</li>
<li>Which rule explains the current state?</li>
<li>What are the current QQQ and QLD prices and trend indicators?</li>
<li>When was the last model trade or model action?</li>
</ol>

<h2>2. Daily Data Source and Timing</h2>

<table>
<tr><th>Item</th><th>Rule</th></tr>
<tr><td>Market data</td><td>Free end-of-day adjusted close data from the Yahoo Finance chart API.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Symbols</td><td>QQQ for signal and trend conditions. QLD for leveraged ETF entry and risk checks.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Update time</td><td>Every day at 6:00 PM New York time. GitHub Actions uses UTC scheduling.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Live signal history</td><td>Use real QQQ and QLD data. Do not use synthetic QLD history for live decisions.</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>3. Model States</h2>

<table>
<tr><th>State</th><th>Dashboard Status</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>
<tr><td>Cash</td><td>Hold Cash</td><td>No QQQ or QLD position. Waiting for recovery and risk conditions.</td></tr>
<tr><td>QQQ</td><td>Hold QQQ</td><td>Market recovery has started, but leverage conditions are not yet confirmed.</td></tr>
<tr><td>QQQ + QLD</td><td>DCA to QLD</td><td>Temporary 5-day transition from QQQ into QLD.</td></tr>
<tr><td>QLD</td><td>Hold QLD</td><td>Trend and risk conditions support 2x QLD exposure.</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>4. Exact Strategy Rules</h2>

<h3>Cash to QQQ</h3>
<p>When the model is in Cash, buy QQQ when all conditions are true:</p>
<ul>
<li>QQQ price is above EMA200.</li>
<li>QQQ closes above its prior 20-day high.</li>
<li>QQQ 20-day annualized volatility is below 30%.</li>
</ul>

<h3>QQQ to QLD: 5-Day DCA</h3>
<p>When the model is already in QQQ, begin converting QQQ into QLD when all conditions are true:</p>
<ul>
<li>QQQ EMA50 is above QQQ EMA200.</li>
<li>QQQ 20-day annualized volatility is less than or equal to 25%.</li>
<li>QQQ EMA200 deviation is less than or equal to 20%.</li>
<li>QLD closes above its prior 20-day high.</li>
</ul>

<table>
<tr><th>DCA Day</th><th>Action</th></tr>
<tr><td>Day 1</td><td>Convert 1/5 of remaining QQQ value into QLD.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Day 2</td><td>Convert 1/4 of remaining QQQ value into QLD.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Day 3</td><td>Convert 1/3 of remaining QQQ value into QLD.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Day 4</td><td>Convert 1/2 of remaining QQQ value into QLD.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Day 5</td><td>Convert all remaining QQQ value into QLD.</td></tr>
</table>

<p>If QLD entry conditions fail during DCA, reset the DCA counter. If any exit rule triggers, stop DCA and move to Cash.</p>

<h3>QLD to QQQ: Reduce Leverage</h3>
<p>When QQQ EMA200 deviation is greater than 20%, reduce from QLD to QQQ. This is not a full exit; it reduces from 2x exposure to 1x exposure.</p>

<h3>QQQ to QLD Again</h3>
<p>After reducing from QLD to QQQ, use 5-day DCA back into QLD when all conditions are true:</p>
<ul>
<li>QQQ EMA200 deviation is less than 15%.</li>
<li>QLD closes above its prior 20-day high.</li>
<li>QLD entry conditions remain valid.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Any Position to Cash</h3>
<p>Move to Cash if any one of these risk exit rules is true:</p>
<ul>
<li>QQQ closes below EMA200.</li>
<li>QLD closes below its prior 20-day low.</li>
<li>QQQ 20-day annualized volatility is greater than 35%.</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Dashboard Indicators</h2>

<table>
<tr><th>Indicator</th><th>Meaning</th></tr>
<tr><td>QQQ close</td><td>Adjusted close for the signal ETF.</td></tr>
<tr><td>QLD close</td><td>Adjusted close for the leveraged ETF used for entries and risk checks.</td></tr>
<tr><td>SMA200</td><td>Long-term QQQ trend reference shown on the dashboard.</td></tr>
<tr><td>EMA50 / EMA200</td><td>Trend confirmation used for QLD entry.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Distance above/below SMA200</td><td>Plain trend context for the dashboard.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Distance above/below EMA200</td><td>Used for leverage extension and re-entry rules.</td></tr>
<tr><td>20-day annualized volatility</td><td>Risk filter for Cash to QQQ, QQQ to QLD, and Cash exit rules.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Prior 20-day highs/lows</td><td>Breakout and risk levels for QQQ and QLD.</td></tr>
<tr><td>MACD</td><td>Display-only context. MACD is not part of the trading rule unless promoted later.</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>6. What To Do By Dashboard Status</h2>

<table>
<tr><th>Status</th><th>Operating Action</th></tr>
<tr><td>Hold Cash</td><td>Stay in cash. Do not buy QQQ or QLD until Cash-to-QQQ conditions trigger.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Hold QQQ</td><td>Hold 1x QQQ. Wait for QLD entry conditions or a risk exit.</td></tr>
<tr><td>DCA to QLD</td><td>Follow the current DCA day instruction. If conditions fail, reset DCA and return to QQQ.</td></tr>
<tr><td>Hold QLD</td><td>Hold QLD unless an extension reduction or cash exit rule triggers.</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>7. Dashboard Files</h2>

<table>
<tr><th>File</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
<tr><td>index.html</td><td>Live GitHub Pages dashboard.</td></tr>
<tr><td>data/signals.json</td><td>Current dashboard data and recent history.</td></tr>
<tr><td>data/signals.csv</td><td>Full daily signal history.</td></tr>
<tr><td>scripts/update_signals.py</td><td>Daily update script.</td></tr>
<tr><td>.github/workflows/daily-update.yml</td><td>GitHub Actions schedule for daily updates.</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>8. Weekly Review Checklist</h2>

<ul>
<li>Confirm the latest dashboard date matches the latest available market close.</li>
<li>Confirm QQQ and QLD prices updated successfully.</li>
<li>Check whether the model state changed.</li>
<li>If a real trade was placed, record actual fill prices and shares separately.</li>
<li>Confirm any manual override is written down with the reason.</li>
</ul>

<h2>9. Important Operating Notes</h2>

<ul>
<li>The dashboard is a signal display, not financial advice.</li>
<li>The model uses adjusted close data, so intraday prices may disagree with the dashboard before the next update.</li>
<li>QQQ is the signal source. Do not accidentally switch the signal source to QLD.</li>
<li>QLD is the leveraged holding. Do not use synthetic QLD for live decisions.</li>
<li>MACD is visible for context only.</li>
</ul>

</body>
</html>
